Aubrey Lee was my Great-Grandfather and he grew up to be racist, like his family, but then came WWII and my Great-Grandaddy joined the 82nd Airborne. He jumped into France as a Sergeant very late at night on June 5th 1944. He fought his way across France, Belgium, The Netherlands (in Operation Market Garden), and finally earning the Purple Heart during the Battle of The Bulge from shrapnel from a German grenade that sent him home and he walked with a slight limp for the rest of his life after that   Somewhere along the way in the confusion of war he ended up fighting next to Black American soldiers and found they were not different from him and lost his prejudice. He came home changed in many ways and that was one.   From there he voted for Ike twice helping him win Texas twice, as Eisenhower won several former Confederate states in his two elections, and from there the South changed.
